gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 112, Rockets 95
gameRecap.excerpt: Oklahoma City wins their 6th straight game as they defeat Houston, 112-95. For Oklahoma, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander (31 points (four 3PM), eight rebounds, three assists), Jalen Williams (24 points, five rebounds, five assists, two steals), and Chet Holmgren (18 points, 13 rebounds, three blocks) combine for 73 to lead the way in the victory. Alperen Sengun led the way with 23 points, 11 rebounds, six assists, and two blocks while Jabari Smith Jr. tallied 18 points and 13 rebounds for Houston in the losing effort. Oklahoma City wins and improves to 41-17 on the season, while Houston moves to 25-33 with the loss.
